 Permission or agreement. It is a voluntary actby a person, willingly given to another person or persons. Consent to have sex is:
- The verbal presence of a YES;and not the quiet absence of a NO;
- YES must be ongoing in every and any type of sexual act;
- YES to some sexual acts does not constitute consent to all forms of sexual acts;
- Any person participating in any sexual act has the right to revoke YES, i.e. say NO at any timefor whatever reason or no reason at all;
-NO by a person at any point in any sexual act is a NO, which the other person or person mustrespect, it�s not a choice;
-YES, to have sex cannot be assumed or implied, even if you are in a relationship;
-YES cannot be obtained if either parties is asleep, mentally or physically incapacitated temporarily due to alcohol or drugs or other conditions;
-YES is acceptable only if the person saying it is in full possession and exercise of sufficient mental capacity to make an informed and intelligent choice to do something proposed by another person or persons;
Consent or a consensual act, it is always positive, an enthusiastic affirmation that both people and/or more have mutually agreed to engage in the activity.

  Permission or agreement is not given voluntarily by a person or persons to another person or persons. It always means the act in whatever form or type is unwelcome. There is no consent:
When an act or agreement is against a person or persons will;
When an act is done by person or persons both known or unknown, by the use of fear, threats, force or other forms of coercion of the victim, guardian or custodian; 
When an act represents abduction, fraud, manipulation, deception or misrepresentation such as enticement, inducement, misinformation, forgery, tricks, coercion, hostage, allurement, influence, abuse of power and by any means of inducement; 
When acts lead to death, disability, injury, or physical and mental harm. This includes the use of threats to withhold a benefit to which the person being threatened is entitled to by custom or law;
When the person or persons is incapable of giving consent because of his/her youth or because of his/her temporary or permanent mental or physical incapacity.
All acts and forms of Gender Based Violence involve no consent and each one of them is termed a non-consensual act (rape,sexual assault, physical assault, denial of resources andopportunities, psychological/emotional abuse). Acts of such violence can take many forms (domestic violence - intimate partner violence and inter-generational violence,incest,child sexual abuse, sexual exploitation, sexual harassment or transactional sex,sexual slavery, human trafficking) and can be one off or continuing over time. In expanded form, harmful tradition practices (child marriage, forced marriage,polygamy and bigamy, chaupadi, untouchability, accusation of witchcraft etc) also fall within the remit of GBV.  If reported, there is legal recourse in Nepal and when proven, there is also criminal punishment.
